                            else table.insert(MD.Value, val) end 
                            BtnLbl.Text = getLabel(); Build() 
                            if opts.Callback then opts.Callback(MD.Value) end 
                        end) 
                    end 
                    List.CanvasSize = UDim2.new(0, 0, 0, ListLayout.AbsoluteContentSize.Y) 
                end 
 
                BtnF.MouseButton1Click:Connect(function() 
                    open = not open 
                    if open then 
                        Build() 
                        local h = math.min(#MD.Values * 24 + 40, 180) 
                        Tween(Wrap, {Size = UDim2.new(1, 0, 0, h)}, 0.3) 
                        Arr2.Text = "▲" 
                        Tween(bfs2, {Color = AuraUI.Theme.Primary}, 0.1) 
                    else 
                        Tween(Wrap, {Size = UDim2.new(1, 0, 0, 36)}, 0.25) 
                        Arr2.Text = "▼" 
                        Tween(bfs2, {Color = AuraUI.Theme.Stroke}, 0.1) 
                    end 
                end) 
 
                function MD:Refresh(newVals) 
                    MD.Values = newVals or MD.Values 
                    local nVal = {} 
                    for _, v in ipairs(MD.Value) do if table.find(MD.Values, v) then table.insert(nVal, v) end end 
                    MD.Value = nVal; BtnLbl.Text = getLabel() 
                    if open then Build() end 
                end 
 
                function MD:Set(v) MD.Value = v; BtnLbl.Text = getLabel(); if open then Build() end end 
 
                AuraUI.Options[id] = MD 
                return MD 
            end 
 
            -- ── Label ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── 
            function GB:AddLabel(text) 
                local L = Instance.new("TextLabel") 
                L.Size = UDim2.new(1, 0, 0, 16); L.BackgroundTransparency = 1 
                L.Text = text; L.Font = Enum.Font.Gotham; L.TextSize = 12 
                L.TextXAlignment = Enum.TextXAlignment.Left; L.Parent = Cnt 
                Reg(L, "TextColor3", "TextDim") 
                return L 
            end 
 
            -- ── Separator ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── 
            function GB:AddSeparator() 
                local S = Instance.new("Frame") 
                S.Size = UDim2.new(1, 0, 0, 1); S.BorderSizePixel = 0 
                S.BackgroundColor3 = AuraUI.Theme.Stroke; S.Parent = Cnt 
                Reg(S, "BackgroundColor3", "Stroke") 
            end 
 
            return GB 
        end -- MakeGroupbox 
 
        function TD:AddGroupbox(name)      return MakeGroupbox(TD._LeftCol, name) end 
        function TD:AddLeftGroupbox(name)  return MakeGroupbox(TD._LeftCol, name) end 
        function TD:AddRightGroupbox(name) return MakeGroupbox(TD._RightCol, name) end 
 
        return TD 
    end -- AddTab 
 
    -- ── Settings tab  (always added last) ──────────────────────────────────── 
    -- Deferred: user calls AddTab for their tabs first, then CreateWindow 
    -- adds Settings automatically. We use a flag to ensure it's only added once. 
    local settingsAdded = false 
    local function EnsureSettings() 
        if settingsAdded then return end 
        settingsAdded = true 
 
        local SetTab  = WD:AddTab("Settings") 
        local ThemeGB = SetTab:AddLeftGroupbox("Theme") 
        local CfgGB   = SetTab:AddRightGroupbox("Config") 
 
        local themeNames = {} 
        for k in pairs(AuraUI.Themes) do table.insert(themeNames, k) end 
 
        ThemeGB:AddDropdown("ThemeDrop", { 
            Title    = "Hub Theme", 
            Values   = themeNames, 
            Default  = AuraUI.CurrentThemeName, 
            Callback = function(val) 
                AuraUI.CurrentThemeName = val 
                UpdateTheme() 
            end 
        }) 
 
        AuraUI:_InitConfigUI(CfgGB) 
    end 
 
    -- Wrap AddTab so that every time the user adds a tab, we schedule 
    -- Settings to be appended after the current execution cycle. 
    local origAddTab = WD.AddTab 
    local settingsScheduled = false 
    WD.AddTab = function(self, name, icon) 
        local td = origAddTab(self, name, icon) 
        if name ~= "Settings" and not settingsScheduled then 
            settingsScheduled = true 
            task.defer(function() 
                settingsScheduled = false 
                EnsureSettings() 
            end) 
        end 
        return td 
    end 
 
    return WD 
end 
 
-- ─── Notifications ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── 
function AuraUI:Notify(opts) 
    task.spawn(function() 
        PlaySound(AuraUI.Sounds.Notify, 0.3, 1) 
        local T = AuraUI.Theme 
 
        local note = Instance.new("Frame") 
        note.Size = UDim2.new(0, 255, 0, 50) 
        note.Position = UDim2.new(1, 10, 1, -64) 
        note.BackgroundColor3 = T.Groupbox 
        note.BorderSizePixel = 0 
        note.Parent = (gethui and gethui()) or CoreGui 
        Corner(note, 5) 
        MakeStroke(note, T.Primary, 1) 
 
        local Stripe = Instance.new("Frame") 
        Stripe.Size = UDim2.new(0, 3, 1, 0) 
        Stripe.BackgroundColor3 = T.Primary 
        Stripe.BorderSizePixel = 0; Stripe.Parent = note 
        Corner(Stripe, 2) 
 
        local title = Instance.new("TextLabel") 
        title.Size = UDim2.new(1, -18, 0, 17) 
        title.Position = UDim2.new(0, 12, 0, 8) 
        title.BackgroundTransparency = 1 
        title.Text = opts.Title or "Notice" 
        title.Font = Enum.Font.GothamBold; title.TextSize = 13 
        title.TextXAlignment = Enum.TextXAlignment.Left 
        title.TextColor3 = T.Text; title.Parent = note 
 
        local desc = Instance.new("TextLabel") 
        desc.Size = UDim2.new(1, -18, 0, 14) 
        desc.Position = UDim2.new(0, 12, 0, 27) 
        desc.BackgroundTransparency = 1 
        desc.Text = opts.Content or "" 
        desc.Font = Enum.Font.Gotham; desc.TextSize = 11 
        desc.TextXAlignment = Enum.TextXAlignment.Left 
        desc.TextColor3 = T.TextMuted; desc.Parent = note 
 
        Tween(note, {Position = UDim2.new(1,-265,1,-64)}, 0.28, Enum.EasingStyle.Quart, Enum.EasingDirection.Out) 
        task.wait(opts.Duration or 3) 
        Tween(note, {Position = UDim2.new(1,10,1,-64)}, 0.2, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad, Enum.EasingDirection.In) 
        task.delay(0.22, function() note:Destroy() end) 
    end) 
end 
 
-- ─── Config ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── 
function AuraUI:SaveConfig(name) 
    name = name:gsub("[^%w%-_]", "")
    if name == "" then return end
    local data = {} 
    for id, opt in pairs(AuraUI.Options) do 
        local val = opt.Value 
        if typeof(val) == "Color3" then data[id] = {type="Color3",r=val.R,g=val.G,b=val.B} 
        elseif typeof(val) == "EnumItem" then data[id] = {type="EnumItem",name=val.Name} 
        elseif type(val) == "table" then
            local arr = {}
            for _, v in ipairs(val) do table.insert(arr, v) end
            data[id] = {type="Array", values=arr}
        else data[id] = val end 
    end 
    if not isfolder("Aura_Configs") then makefolder("Aura_Configs") end 
    writefile("Aura_Configs/"..name..".json", HttpService:JSONEncode(data)) 
    AuraUI:Notify({Title="Config Saved", Content="Saved as '"..name.."'", Duration=2}) 
end 
 
function AuraUI:LoadConfig(name) 
    name = name:gsub("[^%w%-_]", "")
    if name == "" then return end
    local path = "Aura_Configs/"..name..".json" 
    if isfile and isfile(path) then 
        local ok, data = pcall(function() return HttpService:JSONDecode(readfile(path)) end) 
        if not ok then AuraUI:Notify({Title="Error", Content="Corrupt config.", Duration=2}); return end 
        for id, val in pairs(data) do 
            local opt = AuraUI.Options[id] 
            if opt and opt.Set then 
                if type(val)=="table" then
                    if val.type=="Color3" then opt:Set(Color3.new(val.r,val.g,val.b)) 
                    elseif val.type=="EnumItem" then 
                        pcall(function() opt:Set(Enum.KeyCode[val.name]) end)
                    elseif val.type=="Array" then opt:Set(val.values)
                    end
                else opt:Set(val) end 
            end 
        end 
        AuraUI:Notify({Title="Config Loaded", Content="Loaded '"..name.."'", Duration=2}) 
    else 
        AuraUI:Notify({Title="Error", Content="Config not found.", Duration=2}) 
    end 
end 

function AuraUI:DeleteConfig(name)
    name = name:gsub("[^%w%-_]", "")
    if name == "" then return end
    local path = "Aura_Configs/" .. name .. ".json"
    if isfile and isfile(path) then
        local delfile = delfile or (syn and syn.write_file and function(p) writefile(p, "") end) or function() end
        pcall(function() delfile(path) end)
        AuraUI:Notify({Title = "Config Deleted", Content = "Removed '" .. name .. "'", Duration = 2})
    end
end
 
function AuraUI:GetConfigs() 
    if not isfolder("Aura_Configs") then 
        if makefolder then makefolder("Aura_Configs") end; return {} 
    end 
    local files = listfiles("Aura_Configs") or {} 
    local names = {} 
    for _, f in ipairs(files) do 
        local stripped = f:match("[/\\]?([^/\\]+)$") or f 
        stripped = stripped:gsub("%.json$", "") 
        if stripped ~= "" then 
            table.insert(names, stripped) 
        end 
    end 
    return names 
end 
 
function AuraUI:_InitConfigUI(GB) 
    local ci = "" 
    GB:AddInput("NewCfgName", {Title="Config Name", Placeholder="my_settings", Callback=function(v) ci=v end}) 
    
    local function reloadDropdown()
        if AuraUI.ConfigListDropdown then
            AuraUI.ConfigListDropdown.Values = AuraUI:GetConfigs()
            AuraUI.ConfigListDropdown:Refresh()
        end
    end

    GB:AddButton({Title="Save Config", Callback=function() 
        if ci ~= "" then 
            AuraUI:SaveConfig(ci) 
            reloadDropdown()
        else AuraUI:Notify({Title="Error", Content="Enter a name first!", Duration=2}) end 
    end}) 
    GB:AddSeparator() 
    
    AuraUI.ConfigListDropdown = GB:AddDropdown("LoadCfgDrop", {Title="Load Config", Values=AuraUI:GetConfigs(), Default=nil}) 
    
    GB:AddButton({Title="Load Selected", Callback=function() 
        local sel = AuraUI.ConfigListDropdown.Value
        if sel and sel ~= "" then AuraUI:LoadConfig(sel) 
        else AuraUI:Notify({Title="Error", Content="Select a config first.", Duration=2}) end 
    end}) 

    GB:AddButton({Title="Overwrite Selected", Callback=function() 
        local sel = AuraUI.ConfigListDropdown.Value
        if sel and sel ~= "" then 
            AuraUI:SaveConfig(sel) 
            reloadDropdown()
        else AuraUI:Notify({Title="Error", Content="Select a config first.", Duration=2}) end 
    end}) 
    
    GB:AddButton({Title="Delete Selected", Callback=function() 
        local sel = AuraUI.ConfigListDropdown.Value
        if sel and sel ~= "" then 
            AuraUI:DeleteConfig(sel) 
            reloadDropdown()
        else AuraUI:Notify({Title="Error", Content="Select a config first.", Duration=2}) end 
    end}) 

    GB:AddButton({Title="Refresh List", Callback=function() 
        reloadDropdown()
        AuraUI:Notify({Title="Refreshed", Content="Config list updated.", Duration=1.5}) 
    end}) 
end 
 
if getgenv then getgenv().AuraUI = AuraUI end
return AuraUI
